Some info about Holland: 

It is possible to take up further studies in Holland in the English language in various disciplines. 

Career opportunities in Holland are very good for Engineers (all branches), IT professionals, Accountants, Finance, Marketing and Customer Service Professionals. 

Career opportunities are also very good for Teachers in International Schools in which the medium of instruction is English. 

Holland is one of the most advanced and internationally oriented countries in Europe. London and Paris can be reached from Amsterdam (capital of Holland) in one hour by a flight. 

Most Indians living in Holland visit India every year to spend time with their relatives. 

Moreover, telephone costs are quite low now-a-days; so one calls one's relatives/friends in India quite often. In addition, one can also make PC to PC and PC to Land-line phone calls worldwide which cost almost nothing. 

There are about 100 Indian families living within 30 kilometres from our house. Hence one can have a good social life with Indians, besides the local Dutch people. 

The working hours in Holland are regulated by law and thus no one works beyond 8 AM to 6 PM for long periods. Only exceptionally, do people work in week-ends as well. Commuting times in Holland are also generally short like 30 minutes or less. Thus, balancing the domestic responsibilities with a professional career is a lot easier in Holland than in India and U. S. A. As a consequence, the overall quality of life is a lot better in Holland than in many western countries.

Moreover, there are a lot of part-time jobs available in Holland in all professions. This also helps to balance the career with domestic responsibilities more easily.

Will provide additional details about Holland if you have interest to proceed further.
